facilities {
  name: "Nepean Sportsplex"
  description:
    "The Nepean Sportsplex hosts 30-plus regional, provincial, national and international sporting events as well as "
    "35 special events per year. Our facility serves over 1.5 million clients annually, who enjoy any of the following "
    "amenities: An impressive aquatic centre with a 50 metre Olympic pool with diving towers and springboards, a "
    "25-metre family pool, a children’s wading pool and a therapeutic whirlpool. The centre also features three North "
    "American size rinks: The Yzerman and the Allen J. MacDonald arenas, and a 10-sheet curling centre. A 3,000 sq. "
    "feet weight room and fitness centre including four squash courts, a studio and gymnasium as well as a large "
    "outdoor Sports field area featuring two baseball diamonds, a soccer field, the Minto sports field turf, a lawn "
    "bowling turf and pavilion as well as outdoor fitness trails. With 18 meeting and banquet rooms ranging from 468 "
    "to 8,640 sq. ft. and available space of 62,000 sq. ft. for conventions, the Nepean Sportsplex has become known as "
    "a top-notch location to hold tradeshows and special events including the annual Christmas craft show. Our Seniors "
    "Centre offers activities for retired adults 50+, while the Visual Arts Centre provides all levels of visual arts "
    "programs. General interest programs complete the options available."
  source {
    url: "https://ottawa.ca/en/recreation-and-parks/facilities/place-listing/nepean-sportsplex"
    _date {
      seconds: 1752022276
    }
  }
  address:
    "1701 Woodroffe Avenue\n"
    "Ottawa ON K2G 1W2\n"
    "Canada"
  _lnglat {
    lng: -75.74529
    lat: 45.327126
  }
